==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trainband
<hw>Train"band`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Trainbands</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A band or company of an
organized military force instituted by James I. and dissolved by Charles
II.; -- afterwards applied to the London militia.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He felt that, without some better protection than that of the
<qex>trainbands</qex> and Beefeaters, his palace and person would hardly
be secure.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>trainband</qex> captain eke was he⟦br⟧
Of famous London town.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trainbearer</ent>⟦br⟧
